name: Gerardo Velasquez
tweet: Most have lost so much oxygen that they're practically brain dead. They will not recover from this, but family is too heartbroken to pull the plug, so they stay in the ICU for months, just kept alive by ventilators and meds.

name: Gerardo Velasquez
tweet: All beds taken up by covid patients, people with other conditions have been scattered around to other units.  They require so much oxygen, at one point, it caused a fluctuation in pressure throughout the hospital that affected the NICU and almost hurt the newborns in that unit.
